    • Field Detail

      • ANY_IP

        public static final java.lang.String ANY_IP
        Normally, the Gatekeeper IP address to be used for the device's registration is resolved when you get the DeviceID. If you wish to delay the resolution of the Gatekeeper IP address until the actual registration, you may do so by setting the SwitchName to a valid "Switch Connection" and the SwitchIPInterface to ANY_IP in the GetDeviceId request. This strategy gives you the advantage of being able to try a different Gateway IP address for a failed device registration, without the need to issue a ReleaseDeviceId followed by another GetDeviceId.
